FBIS4-17015 "drsov077_b_94045" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Russians Holding 10-15 Million U.S. Dollars Russians Holding 10-15 Million U.S. Dollars LD2004202594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 1600 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004202594 Moscow Russian Television Network Russian BFN [From the "Vesti" newscast] [Text] Speaking today at the pariamentary hearings on the country's foreign economic activities, Viktor Melnikov, head of the Main Directorate for Currency Regulations of the Russian Central Bank, quoted some interesting figures. According to Melnikov, at present Russian citizens have on their hands between 10 and 15 million U.S. dollars in cash, the purchasing power of which exceeds that of the total cash in rubles currently in circulation. Melnikov said that some of the reasons for such wealth of the Russians are illegal currency operations, tax evasion, and ever-increasing quantities of counterfeit dollars in circulation.
